cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper is about Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are commonly used in machine learning for image generation and other tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since GANs are often used for image generation. The paper also discusses theoretical analysis and empirical experiments, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the proposed test for estimating the support size of the generated distribution could be considered under cs.SD (Sound).
